 7.208080405383694e-13, \"text\": \"Queenslander\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queensland_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queensland_rugby_league_team\"}, {\"begin\": 914, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_No_1\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.872366634773295e-14, \"text\": \"Shadow Man\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_No_1\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_No_1\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Toowoomba's Burton, now based in Great Britain, was lying third overnight after the dressage and cross country sections but moved into the silver-medal position after Monday's qualifying round.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toowoomba\", \"score\": 0.9999998717171448, \"rank\": 1.1751920901663304e-07, \"text\": \"Toowoomba\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toowoomba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toowoomba\"}, {\"begin\": 965, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\", \"score\": 0.8726333154727054, \"rank\": 0.10324113772307947, \"text\": \"Burton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\"}, {\"begin\": 986, \"end\": 999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998203576660647, \"rank\": 9.529158501316144e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then on a blazingly hot afternoon against the majestic backdrop of the Chateau, Burton and Shadow Man had no fences down again in the finale to put the pressure on the last rider to go, three-time Olympic champion Michael Jung.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\", \"score\": 0.8726333154727054, \"rank\": 0.10324113772307947, \"text\": \"Burton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\"}, {\"begin\": 1239, \"end\": 1249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_No_1\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.872366634773295e-14, \"text\": \"Shadow Man\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_No_1\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_No_1\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christopher Burton won team bronze in Rio eight years ago.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1389, \"end\": 1395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\", \"score\": 0.8726333154727054, \"rank\": 0.10324113772307947, \"text\": \"Burton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burton_Snowboards\"}, {\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998794789389869, \"rank\": 0.00012053558791279685, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Getty Images: Mike Hewitt)  Burton was in sight of earning Australia's first individual eventing triumph since Matt Ryan piloted Kibah Tic Toc to victory in Barcelona 1992.\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1450, \"end\": 1461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Hewitt_(footballer)\", \"score\": 0.99998169007568